# Live hero terminal ("Press ⏎ to get a computer") config.
#
# EASIEST: from the repo root just run
#     npm run dev:demo
# which auto-opens the SSH tunnel to the box, reads the token from
# ~/.config/latitude, health-checks boringd, and starts the app — no env needed.
#
# MANUAL: if you'd rather set it yourself, open a tunnel to the box:
#     ssh -N -L 18080:localhost:8080 root@<box-ip> -i ~/.ssh/boring_latitude
# then run:
#     BORING_URL=http://localhost:18080 BORING_TOKEN=<token> npm run dev -w web
BORING_URL=http://localhost:18080
BORING_TOKEN=
